{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3535191,"name":"Noah Simon","username":"tubularturtle8","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/tubularturtle8/{size}/209634_2.png","created_at":"2025-02-21T10:50:46.297Z","cooked":"<p>I am currently working on tuning my team‚Äôs elevator, and have run into an extremely strange issue. It is working with a Profiled <span class="abbreviation">PID<template class="tooltiptext" data-text="Proportional Integral Derivative"></template></span> controller, and it seemingly, everytime it switches from accelerating or constant (maximum) velocity to decelerating, <strong>shuts down motors with 0 current. Notably, the motors do not have 0 applied voltage.</strong> This results in a short and sudden drop of the elevator as it stops moving without any applied current.</p>
<p>A graph of applied output (bus voltage * duty cycle) alongside the current graph is pasted below. White is current, orange is applied output.<br>
<div class="lightbox-wrapper"><a class="lightbox" href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/d/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71.png" data-download-href="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71" title="image"><img src="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/d/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71_2_679x500.png" alt="image" data-base62-sha1="1SP8qCKmJWXnet2R6iPqGlJXM7D" width="679" height="500" srcset="https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/optimized/3X/0/d/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71_2_679x500.png, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/d/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71.png 1.5x, https://www.chiefdelphi.com/uploads/default/original/3X/0/d/0d34b58b26f9fea274a55a45537e1dc3dc9a1a71.png 2x" data-dominant-color="2B2A29"><div class="meta"><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#far-image"></use></svg><span class="filename">image</span><span class="informations">985√ó725 47.1 KB</span><svg class="fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#discourse-expand"></use></svg></div></a></div></p>
<p>Does anyone have any idea what is going on and how I can try to fix this issue?</p>
<p>As a potential seperate issue, the applied voltage isn‚Äôt updating according to the input voltage (input from the code) until around 40 ms later. I would expect it to be no greater than 20ms as that is the loop time of the code. Any ideas there?</p>
